+- Pass all unit tests.
+- Performance suitable for large grids.
+
+Approach:
+1. Parse grid dimensions, locate source.
+2. Use DP (dynamic programming) storing number of ways to reach each cell with each direction (down, down-left, down-right) as bigint.
+3. Iterate rows top‑to‑bottom, propagating ways to next cells. When encountering a splitter '^', split current ways into two outgoing directions.
+4. For countBeamCells, also track a Set of visited cell coordinates whenever any ways > 0 reach a cell.
+5. Accumulate exit paths when a propagation steps out of bounds.
+6. Return visited set size and total exit paths.
+
+Key Files:
+- src/index.ts: implementation of both functions.
+- src/index.test.ts: unit tests (already added).
+
+Risks:
+- Large bigint additions may be costly but acceptable for ≤200 rows × 200 cols × 3 dirs.
+- Ensure source cell counts as visited.
+- Handle empty grid and source on bottom row.
+
+---
